>Yes there is: consistency in context.  We are talking about
>computers, and everything else is in powers of two.
No, it's not.  When you talk about 10Mbps Ethernet, that's 10*1000*1000 bits 
per second.  The only place powers of 2 makes sense is when address lines are 
involved (ie RAM).
